{"parentUuid":"4bcaf4e4-1569-4e93-933b-c574a9b4d1fa","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"f7a7582b-7162-41b4-a238-8d0c144e4a77","agentId":"aa4eeee267b375df0","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XzFMWDS82QTgnaDKUzLVeU","type":"tool_result","content":"origin/main\nfeature/quota-admin\nef3fb3f686649d0ee0d37707dd61013b5e1d28f4","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"d0cc3c63-0e16-4bca-9d6c-02c3dbc53e67","timestamp":"2026-07-10T04:17:21.613Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"4bcaf4e4-1569-4e93-933b-c574a9b4d1fa","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"e247e36e-cf5c-45a2-ad59-d72d8d34e0a5","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"f7a7582b-7162-41b4-a238-8d0c144e4a77","agentId":"aa4eeee267b375df0","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01F7aiMGifxPVSoVftckot8A","type":"tool_result","content":"# Quota administration — GET /v1/quotas (list) + DELETE /v1/quotas (remove)\n\n## Summary\n\nCompletes the quota-admin CRUD started by the shipped `metric-quotas` feature (`PUT /v1/quotas`).\nAdds two admin-scoped, tenant-isolated surfaces on the same `/v1/quotas` path: `GET /v1/quotas`\nreturns the caller's full, unpaginated, deterministically ordered quota list; `DELETE\n/v1/quotas?customer_id=X&metric=Y` removes one cap, returning 204 on success or an explicit 404 if\nno such quota exists in the caller's tenant (not silently idempotent). Both reuse the existing\n`_require_admin_and_throttled` dependency chain, the same anchored `customer_id`/`metric`\nallowlists, `scoped_transaction`, and the `quotas_tenant_isolation` FORCE-RLS policy the shipped\n`PUT` already established — no new table, no new Alembic migration, no new credential, and no\nchange to `POST /v1/events` behavior beyond deletion removing the cap (never the recorded\n`usage_rollup` counters). See `.pipeline/plan.md` for the full design rationale and its STRIDE\nthreat model (also mirrored in `docs/system_architecture.md`'s \"Request flow — `GET`/`DELETE\n/v1/quotas`\" section).\n\n## Changes\n\n- **API layer** (`src/api/routes/quotas.py`, `src/api/schemas/quotas.py`, `src/api/middleware.py`):\n  new `GET`/`DELETE /v1/quotas` handlers on the existing router; new `QuotaDeleteParams` query-param\n  schema (reuses `QuotaPutRequest`'s `CustomerId`/`Metric` allowlists, `extra='forbid'`); `DELETE`\n  added to CORS `allow_methods` (inert — empty origin allowlist, server-to-server API).\n- **Service layer** (`src/services/quota_service.py`): new `list_tenant_quotas(principal)` and\n  `delete_tenant_quota(principal, params)`; the latter raises `HTTPException(404)` on no match and\n  logs `quota.delete` INFO on success.\n- **Repository layer** (`src/repositories/quotas_repo.py`): new `list_quotas(session, *,\n  api_key_id)` (ordered, tenant-scoped `SELECT`) and `delete_quota(session, *, api_key_id,\n  customer_id, metric)` (parameterized `DELETE ... RETURNING customer_id`, returns whether a row\n  matched).\n- **Security fix included in this diff** (found and fixed by the security stage, not part of the\n  planned feature scope): `.gitignore` was missing a `.terraform/` entry, so ~108 MB of vendored\n  Terraform provider binaries were entering the diff-scoped change set as untracked files. Added\n  `.terraform/` to `.gitignore`; the committable `infra/.terraform.lock.hcl` (provider pinning) is\n  deliberately left un-ignored.\n- **Docs**: this stage — `docs/system_architecture.md`, `src/api/README.md`,\n  `src/services/README.md`, `src/repositories/README.md`, `tests/README.md`,\n  `tests/integration/README.md`.\n\n## Decisions & tradeoffs\n\n- **DELETE-not-found → 404, not idempotent-204.** A retried DELETE of an already-removed quota\n  returns 404 on the second call — the brief-sanctioned \"deletes are explicit\" contract, and\n  indistinguishable from a cross-tenant delete attempt (both correctly refuse to act; see BOLA note\n  below).\n- **No synchronization added between DELETE and an in-flight `POST /v1/events`.** Both contend on\n  the same quota-row lock (the DELETE's implicit lock vs. the ingest's `SELECT ... FOR UPDATE OF\n  q`), so PostgreSQL serializes them; whichever commits first determines the outcome for reads that\n  follow. This is the brief-accepted same race `PUT`'s replacement semantics already have — no\n  advisory lock, barrier, or usage reset was added.\n- **GET carries no dedicated audit log.** Plan's Open Question 1, resolved to \"no log\" — a plain\n  read of the caller's own config, mirroring `GET /v1/usage`'s precedent (reads don't emit business\n  events; DELETE, a destructive action, does).\n- **Unpaginated GET list.** Accepted per the brief on the assumption that per-tenant quota counts\n  stay small (bounded by admin `PUT` volume); pagination/filtering is a hard out-of-scope exclusion.\n\n## Testing\n\n**Acceptance criteria: 18 test-covered + 1 delegated to security = 19 total** (source:\n`.pipeline/test-results.json` `criteria_covered.by_id`; delegated = entries with `delegated:\n\"security\"`). AC18 (ASVS 5.0.0 reconciliation across the change set) is the security stage's\ndeliverable, not a test-suite assertion — confirmed reconciled in `.pipeline/security-report.md`\n(section 6g), not counted as test-covered.\n\n- **Suite result:** 216/217 passed. The 1 failure —\n  `tests/integration/test_usage_export_perf.py::test_export_p95_timing_meets_the_confirmed_3000ms_budget_at_the_row_cap`\n  — is a **pre-existing** hard-coded p95 timing assert from the already-merged `usage-export`\n  feature (last touched at `bcf16bb`, not in this branch's diff). It has no `@pytest.mark.perf`\n  marker, so it rides `pipeline-ci.yml`'s unfiltered test job. Re-measured this run at p95 3763ms vs.\n  its 3000ms budget, on a dev machine under concurrent Docker/CPU contention (four unrelated\n  containers running); this is a follow-up for the deployment/human owner, **not part of this\n  diff**.\n- **Coverage:** 88.15% lines, **66.67% branches** (combined; gate is `--cov-fail-under=85` on the\n  line figure, met). New/changed feature modules (`routes/quotas.py`, `schemas/quotas.py`,\n  `quota_service.py`) are 100% line-covered; `quotas_repo.py` sits at 71% branch coverage, attributed\n  in `test-results.json` to a coverage.py partial-branch artifact on multi-line return statements\n  that every call-path test does exercise (empty list, multi-row list, delete-found/not-found) —\n  matching an identical pre-existing pattern on the sibling `read_tenant_quota_state_locked`.\n- **Test-pyramid shape:** `pyramid` (project default), realized as 6 unit (schema validation) + 20\n  integration (endpoint/tenancy/concurrency/RLS-backstop) = 26 new tests this feature, out of 217\n  total in the full suite.\n- **Test quality (advisory — `.pipeline/test-quality.json`):** `quality_ok: false`. Mutation testing\n  (mutmut) **could not run** — it refuses to execute natively on Windows (the tool prints a\n  WSL-required message and exits without mutating anything; `scope: []`, not a silently-shrunk\n  measurement). The CI mutation job exists but is `if: false`-gated pending config; mutation coverage\n  for `quotas_repo.py`/`quota_service.py`/`routes/quotas.py`/`schemas/quotas.py` has genuinely never\n  run anywhere yet — flagged honestly rather than a false \"quality_ok: true\". Adversarial-review\n  notable gaps (all low severity except mutation, which is medium): DELETE's own 429 throttle\n  exhaustion is untested (only GET is driven to 429; DELETE is only proven *not* throttled while\n  under capacity); no wrong-type/repeated-query-param coercion test for DELETE's `customer_id`/\n  `metric`; ordering test doesn't probe a same-collation-adjacent-value case; the GET/DELETE\n  forced-error tests monkeypatch at the service layer, not inside the repository's own `text()`\n  execute call.\n\n## Security\n\nScope: diff against `HEAD` (`ef3fb3f`). **Clean — 0 critical findings**, 2 non-blocking warnings:\n1. `CVE-2025-71176` (pytest 8.3.4, dev/test-only dependency, not in the runtime container) — CVSS\n   ~6.8, below the ≥7.0 deploy-gate floor. Safe version `>= 9.0.3`; not auto-bumped per policy (human\n   decides on `pyproject.toml`/`poetry.lock`).\n2. Pre-existing, out-of-diff-scope note: the Tier-1 pre-auth throttle keys on `request.client.host`\n   with no proxy-header trust configured, so behind the ALB it would bucket per-node rather than\n   per-real-client. Not introduced by this diff (only CORS `DELETE` touches `middleware.py` here);\n   the effective anti-abuse control for these admin routes is Tier-2 (principal-keyed, proven by\n   AC12).\n\nSTRIDE: 10/10 mechanisms verified present and efficacy-correct, 0 missing, 0 new unmodeled threats\n(`stride_new_threats: 0`). ASVS 5.0.0 reconciled across triggered chapters V1/V2/V4/V6/V8/V12/V13/\nV14/V16, including in-scope L3 V8.2.x (object-level authorization / BOLA), proven by the\ncross-tenant-DELETE→404 test (AC8) plus the adversarial RLS-backstop test that strips the\n`api_key_id` filter entirely and shows FORCE RLS alone still confines the DELETE\n(`test_rls_blocks_cross_tenant_delete_when_app_filter_is_absent`).\n\n## Supply chain\n\n- **Lockfile integrity:** clean — no manifest/lockfile drift in the change set (`lockfile-check`).\n- **SBOM:** a CycloneDX SBOM was generated this run (`.pipeline/sbom.cdx.json`), **65 components**.\n  The deployment gate checks this file exists before allowing a deploy.\n\n## Design review (FE Layer 4)\n\nSkipped — API-only project (`CLAUDE.md`: \"Design source: none\"), no design source (`design-approved`\n/ `design-spec.md`) and no `ui.env`. This is a deliberate non-trigger, not a silent gap: there is no\nUI surface for a visual-fidelity/a11y check to run against.\n\n## DAST (runtime)\n\nAdvisory (`.pipeline/dast-review.json`) — OWASP ZAP passive baseline, `target_reached: true`\n(`http://host.docker.internal:8000`, status 200). Alert tally: 0 high, 3 medium, 4 low, 5\ninformational. `over_budget: []`, `within_budget: true` — no severity band exceeded. This is a\npost-GREEN passive scan outside the security loop, not a pass/fail gate; the pre-merge scanners (see\nSecurity above) and human diff review remain the real teeth. Note: the **gating** DAST layers run in\nCI against staging, not in this local run.\n\n## Threat model\n\nSee `.pipeline/plan.md` `## Threat Model` (STRIDE, scoped to this feature) for the full table and\nMermaid DFD. Highest-severity items and their mitigations:\n- **Spoofing / EoP (function-level), High:** unauthenticated or non-admin caller hits GET/DELETE →\n  reused `_require_admin_and_throttled` (Argon2id auth + `scope=='admin'` gate → 403).\n- **Tampering (SQLi), High:** injection via `customer_id`/`metric` DELETE query params → anchored\n  `constr` allowlist rejects at the 422 boundary; parameterized `text()` bind params only.\n- **Info disclosure (GET response), High:** leaking internal fields or another tenant's caps →\n  minimal `response_model=list[QuotaResponse]` + `api_key_id`-scoped SELECT + FORCE RLS.\n- **EoP (IDOR/BOLA), High:** a key deletes another tenant's cap → `api_key_id` filter + FORCE RLS\n  means a cross-tenant DELETE matches zero rows → 404 (cannot see or remove the row at all); proven\n  by AC8 and the RLS-backstop adversarial test.\n- **Info disclosure (safe-error), Medium:** a forced DB exception on GET/DELETE → the existing\n  `handle_unexpected_error` generic-500 catch-all (no leak) + `scoped_transaction` rollback\n  (fail-closed, no partial DELETE) — new criterion AC19, added during the plan-audit revision pass\n  (see `.pipeline/plan-audit.md`).\n\n## Design-record retention\n\nPlan, acceptance criteria, plan-audit, security report, and run-summary for this feature are\narchived under `docs/decisions/feature/quota-admin/` (per `doc-conventions`; `.pipeline/` is\ngitignored and overwritten every feature).","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"91ee32e1-e18c-45eb-9a36-8153d4069181","timestamp":"2026-07-10T04:17:25.298Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"e247e36e-cf5c-45a2-ad59-d72d8d34e0a5","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"6a7d66da-4db1-4dff-8ba1-583694950778","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"f7a7582b-7162-41b4-a238-8d0c144e4a77","agentId":"aa4eeee267b375df0","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Nk6gYzBK8o269KuHVBGKen","type":"tool_result","content":"{\"approved_change_hash\":\"ed2f406bbcc694da2456069939e344c6cce47af9b594b6fa3013e58fd6850a2f\",\"approved_at\":\"2026-07-10T04:16:52Z\",\"note\":\"human diff-review checkpoint (M5)\"}\r\n---\n{\r\n  \"status\": \"pass\",\r\n  \"ran_at\": \"2026-07-10T03:49:38Z\",\r\n  \"scope\": \"diff\",\r\n  \"since_commit\": \"ef3fb3f686649d0ee0d37707dd61013b5e1d28f4\",\r\n  \"tested_change_hash\": \"a5ab12805cc7429fcb55d5b55da7b8663f4bf011c45f3635394f099f989dd308\",\r\n  \"test_strategy\": \"pyramid\",\r\n  \"total\": 217,\r\n  \"passed\": 216,\r\n  \"failed\": 1,\r\n  \"skipped\": {\r\n    \"count\": 0,\r\n    \"tests\": []\r\n  },\r\n  \"failures\": [\r\n    {\r\n      \"name\": \"tests/integration/test_usage_export_perf.py::test_export_p95_timing_meets_the_confirmed_3000ms_budget_at_the_row_cap\",\r\n      \"reason\": \"Pre-existing test from the already-merged usage-export feature (git log shows its last touch at commit bcf16bb, before this branch's diff); it is NOT part of the quota-admin change set (verified this session via `git diff HEAD --name-only` / `git log -- <file>` — the file is untouched by this branch). It is a hard-coded wall-clock p95<=3000ms assert with NO @pytest.mark.perf marker (verified: no perf marker registered anywhere in pyproject.toml or tests/, confirmed via grep this session), so it is not excluded by `-m \\\"not perf\\\"` and also runs unfiltered in pipeline-ci.yml's `poetry run pytest --cov=src --cov-branch --cov-fail-under=85` (no -m flag there either). Re-ran it in isolation twice this session: p95 measured 3763.02ms and similarly over-budget both times, on a dev machine that had four unrelated Docker containers already running concurrently (compounds-openfga, postgres-dev, openemr, phpmyadmin — confirmed via `docker ps` this session) competing for CPU alongside the freshly-started testcontainers Postgres/Redis. This matches the exact machine-load-flake pattern implementation's own progress notes recorded for the sibling test_perf_k6_load.py during this same feature's development. This is a pre-existing, out-of-scope regression risk (its budget was set from a different, less-loaded measurement session) and a real M4P-10 gap (unmarked hard timing assert riding the CI merge gate) — flagged for the human/deployment owner as a follow-up, not fixed here (fixing it would mean editing an unrelated file's test infra / CI config outside this feature's diff, and this session's evidence does not distinguish 'the perf regressed' from 'this dev box was busy' cleanly enough to safely retune the budget).\"\r\n    }\r\n  ],\r\n  \"tests_by_type\": {\r\n    \"unit\": 6,\r\n    \"integration\": 20,\r\n    \"e2e\": 0\r\n  },\r\n  \"tests_by_type_note\": \"Counts are the NEW tests added for this feature (6 in tests/test_schemas_quotas.py::QuotaDeleteParams cases; 19 in tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py + 1 new backstop test appended to tests/integration/test_quotas_rls_backstop.py). Full-suite composition (pre-existing + new) totals 217 tests. The plan declares `pyramid` with an explicit integration-heavy bias for this feature's own tier split (plan.md 'Test strategy' section) because the guarantees under test — ordering, tenant isolation, RLS backstop, fail-closed rollback, per-principal throttling — are only real against actual Postgres/Redis; the schema/validation-only logic (QuotaDeleteParams) stayed unit. This matches the plan's stated rationale, not a silent drift from pyramid.\",\r\n  \"criteria_covered\": {\r\n    \"total\": 19,\r\n    \"covered\": 18,\r\n    \"by_id\": [\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC1\",\r\n        \"covered\": true,\r\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_get_lists_tenant_quotas_ordered_minimal_fields\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"Seeds 3 rows out of insertion order across two customers; asserts exact response body (order + minimal 3-key field set), not just status code.\",\r\n        \"delegated\": null\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC2\",\r\n        \"covered\": true,\r\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_get_is_tenant_isolated\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"Two real tenants (distinct api_key_id), tenant A's GET list asserted to contain only its own row.\",\r\n        \"delegated\": null\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC3\",\r\n        \"covered\": true,\r\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_get_empty_returns_200_empty_list\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"Fresh tenant, no quotas seeded, asserts 200 + [] (not 404).\",\r\n        \"delegated\": null\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC4\",\r\n        \"covered\": true,\r\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_get_ingest_key_forbidden\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"Ingest-scoped key against GET asserts 403 forbidden envelope.\",\r\n        \"delegated\": null\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC5\",\r\n        \"covered\": true,\r\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_get_requires_auth\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"Both no-Authorization-header and an invalid bearer token asserted 401 on GET.\",\r\n        \"delegated\": null\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC6\",\r\n        \"covered\": true,\r\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_existing_returns_204_and_removes_row\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"204 + empty body asserted, then verified via a subsequent GET and a direct raw-table COUNT(*) that the row is actually gone (not merely a status-code check).\",\r\n        \"delegated\": null\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC7\",\r\n        \"covered\": true,\r\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_absent_returns_404_envelope\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"DELETE of a never-seeded (customer_id, metric) asserts 404 not_found, proving the explicit-404 (non-idempotent) decision.\",\r\n        \"delegated\": null\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC8\",\r\n        \"covered\": true,\r\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_cannot_touch_other_tenant + tests/integration/test_quotas_rls_backstop.py::test_rls_blocks_cross_tenant_delete_when_app_filter_is_absent\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"The app-level test proves the IDOR/BOLA outcome (A deleting B's row -> 404, B's row survives) through the real route. The backstop test independently proves WHY: it drops the api_key_id filter entirely and connects as a NOBYPASSRLS role mirroring prod's meterly_app role, and shows the FORCE RLS policy alone still confines the unfiltered DELETE to the caller's tenant -- the adversarial 'disable the primary control, prove the backstop fires' shape, not merely a pass with both controls intact.\",\r\n        \"delegated\": null\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC9\",\r\n        \"covered\": true,\r\n        \"test\": \"tests/test_schemas_quotas.py (QuotaDeleteParams: accepts/missing/mass-assignment/injection-oversized/invalid-metric/hypothesis-property cases) + tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_validation_rejections\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"Unit tier proves the schema boundary in isolation (allowlist regex, extra='forbid', SQLi/traversal/CRLF/oversized payloads all rejected pre-DB); the integration test proves the same rejections surface as 422 validation_failed end-to-end including the unknown-extra-query-param case (api_key_id=999).\",\r\n        \"delegated\": null\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC10\",\r\n        \"covered\": true,\r\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_ingest_key_forbidden\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"Ingest-scoped key against DELETE asserts 403 forbidden.\",\r\n        \"delegated\": null\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC11\",\r\n        \"covered\": true,\r\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_requires_auth\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"Both missing and malformed bearer token asserted 401 on DELETE.\",\r\n        \"delegated\": null\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC12\",\r\n        \"covered\": true,\r\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_quota_admin_routes_rate_limited_per_principal\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"The discriminating adversarial shape: two admin principals share ONE client IP (ASGITransport pinned to 10.0.0.9). Principal A (1 req/s) gets 429 on its second GET; principal B (100 req/s), same IP, still succeeds on both GET and DELETE -- proving the bucket is keyed on api_key_id, not IP. A same-IP-different-owner assertion, not merely 'a different owner on a different IP is unaffected'.\",\r\n        \"delegated\": null\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC13\",\r\n        \"covered\": true,\r\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_does_not_reset_usage_and_events_uncapped\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"Directly reads the raw usage_rollup row before and after the DELETE and asserts total_quantity is byte-identical (5 both times), then proves the cap is genuinely gone by POSTing a 9999-quantity event that would have 429'd under the old cap=10 and asserting 201.\",\r\n        \"delegated\": null\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC14\",\r\n        \"covered\": true,\r\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_no_new_alembic_migration_added\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"Negative assertion: lists alembic/versions/*.py and asserts exactly 3 files exist (0001-0003), so a stray new migration would fail this test. Existing PUT/events/usage suites all still pass unchanged in this same full run.\",\r\n        \"delegated\": null\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC15\",\r\n        \"covered\": true,\r\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_rls_backstop.py::test_rls_blocks_cross_tenant_delete_when_app_filter_is_absent (+ security stage's Semgrep parameterized-SQL check)\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"Same backstop-disabling test as AC8 -- issues the DELETE via a NOBYPASSRLS role with the api_key_id predicate stripped entirely and shows RLS alone still confines it. The parameterized-text()-bind-params claim (no string-built SQL) is a static/Semgrep concern, appropriately left to the security stage's 6c check rather than duplicated here as a test assertion.\",\r\n        \"delegated\": null\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC16\",\r\n        \"covered\": true,\r\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_delete_and_forbidden_are_logged\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"capsys-captured stdout asserts BOTH `quota.delete` is present with `***redacted***` in place of the raw customer_id (proving the structlog facade's centralized redaction fired, per src/logging/__init__.py's _REDACT list which includes customer_id) AND `quota.forbidden` fires on the ingest-key GET.\",\r\n        \"delegated\": null\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC17\",\r\n        \"covered\": true,\r\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_openapi_exposes_get_and_delete_quotas + tests/test_dast_context_documented.py::test_bearer_split_token_auth_context_is_documented\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"First test asserts /openapi.json actually contains both new operations (served schema, not a hand claim); second (pre-existing, still passing) asserts the documented Bearer split-token auth context.\",\r\n        \"delegated\": null\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC18\",\r\n        \"covered\": false,\r\n        \"test\": \"\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"ASVS 5.0.0 reconciliation across the change set is the security stage's deliverable, not a test-suite assertion (per acceptance.md frontmatter delegated_criteria). Copied verbatim from acceptance.md, not invented here.\",\r\n        \"delegated\": \"security\"\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        \"id\": \"AC19\",\r\n        \"covered\": true,\r\n        \"test\": \"tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_get_forced_internal_error_returns_safe_envelope + ::test_delete_forced_internal_error_returns_safe_envelope_and_fails_closed\",\r\n        \"reason\": \"Both monkeypatch the service-layer function to raise RuntimeError and use ASGITransport(raise_app_exceptions=False) to force the real error-handler path; both assert 500/code:internal/requestId present and that the exception class name and message text never leak into the response. The DELETE variant additionally re-reads the raw quotas row afterward and asserts limit_per_window is untouched (42), proving the transaction actually rolled back (fail-closed), not merely that the HTTP response looked generic.\",\r\n        \"delegated\": null\r\n      }\r\n    ]\r\n  },\r\n  \"resilience\": {\r\n    \"migration_roundtrip\": \"n/a\",\r\n    \"property_tests\": 2,\r\n    \"concurrency\": \"pass\"\r\n  },\r\n  \"resilience_note\": \"migration_roundtrip: n/a -- no migration files in this change set (AC14 asserts this negatively, verified above). property_tests: 2 Hypothesis tests total in tests/test_schemas_quotas.py (1 pre-existing for QuotaPutRequest, unchanged; 1 NEW for QuotaDeleteParams -- test_property_delete_customer_id_only_ever_accepts_the_allowlist -- added by this diff), each generating up to 300-char arbitrary text and asserting acceptance implies the anchored regex. concurrency: tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py::test_concurrent_delete_of_the_same_quota_yields_exactly_one_winner fires 10 concurrent DELETEs at the identical (customer_id, metric) via asyncio.gather and 